author: gdaniels
msg: We were failing to convert if the destination class was an array
of > 1 dimension.  Now we convert if the componentType of the
destination is compatible with the source, regardless.  This changed
the behavior converting an Object[] containing an ArrayList into an
Object[][] - you used to get the inner ArrayList flattened into an
Object [], which was the first element of the Object[][].  Now you
get an Object[][] with the ArrayList itself (since it's an Object) at
[0][0].  Changed the test in TestJavaUtils to account for this, and
added a new test to make sure we don't break the behavior.
"ant clean all-tests" passed, so I assume nothing was relying on
